    "problem_statement": "You run a two-factory manufacturing pipeline. Factory A makes components, then Factory B finishes the same jobs.\nEach factory is its own job shop with one-job-per-machine exclusivity and no preemption.\nEvery job must finish all of its Factory A operations before that same job may start any Factory B operation.\nYour objective is to minimize the coupled makespan: the time when the final Factory B operation finishes.\n\nInstance size: 5 jobs, 6 machines in each factory.\nJobs and ordered operations:\n- Job 1: Factory A MA2 (1) -> MA3 (8) -> MA4 (8) -> MA1 (8) -> MA5 (7) -> MA6 (8); Factory B MB1 (4) -> MB2 (7) -> MB5 (2) -> MB3 (8) -> MB6 (4) -> MB4 (1)\n- Job 2: Factory A MA6 (2) -> MA3 (1) -> MA4 (6) -> MA2 (4) -> MA5 (2) -> MA1 (8); Factory B MB6 (9) -> MB3 (4) -> MB1 (3) -> MB4 (2) -> MB2 (9) -> MB5 (1)\n- Job 3: Factory A MA4 (2) -> MA2 (9) -> MA5 (6) -> MA3 (6) -> MA6 (8) -> MA1 (9); Factory B MB3 (4) -> MB5 (5) -> MB6 (3) -> MB2 (6) -> MB1 (9) -> MB4 (5)\n- Job 4: Factory A MA5 (5) -> MA1 (7) -> MA2 (5) -> MA4 (7) -> MA6 (3) -> MA3 (7); Factory B MB3 (2) -> MB6 (3) -> MB2 (1) -> MB4 (4) -> MB1 (3) -> MB5 (5)\n- Job 5: Factory A MA1 (7) -> MA6 (2) -> MA4 (2) -> MA2 (5) -> MA5 (2) -> MA3 (1); Factory B MB2 (2) -> MB6 (2) -> MB4 (9) -> MB3 (9) -> MB5 (6) -> MB1 (3)\n\nConstraints:\n- A machine handles at most one job at a time.\n- Each job must respect its listed operation order inside each factory.\n- Factory B job Jx cannot start until Factory A job Jx has fully completed.\n- When you emit a schedule, every required operation must appear exactly once.\n\nA deterministic feasible baseline schedule is provided below. If you stop immediately or fail to produce a valid schedule, this baseline is what gets scored.\nBaseline makespan: 157\nBaseline schedule summary:\nFactory A: MA1: J1[17-25],J2[55-63],J3[82-91],J4[91-98],J5[98-105]; MA2: J1[0-1],J2[49-53],J3[53-62],J4[98-103],J5[117-122]; MA3: J1[1-9],J2[42-43],J3[68-74],J4[113-120],J5[124-125]; MA4: J1[9-17],J2[43-49],J3[49-51],J4[103-110],J5[115-117]; MA5: J1[25-32],J2[53-55],J3[62-68],J4[68-73],J5[122-124]; MA6: J1[32-40],J2[40-42],J3[74-82],J4[110-113],J5[113-115]\nFactory B: MB1: J1[40-44],J2[78-81],J3[109-118],J4[130-133],J5[154-157]; MB2: J1[44-51],J2[83-92],J3[103-109],J4[125-126],J5[126-128]; MB3: J1[53-61],J2[74-78],J3[91-95],J4[120-122],J5[139-148]; MB4: J1[65-66],J2[81-83],J3[118-123],J4[126-130],J5[130-139]; MB5: J1[51-53],J2[92-93],J3[95-100],J4[133-138],J5[148-154]; MB6: J1[61-65],J2[65-74],J3[100-103],J4[122-125],J5[128-130]\nMakespan: 157\n",
